# ============================================================================
# DOCKER BUILD CONTEXT EXCLUSIONS
# ============================================================================
# When you run `docker build`, Docker sends the entire directory (the "build
# context") to the Docker daemon. This file tells it what to skip.
#
# Why this matters:
#   - node_modules is ~500MB+ — sending it to Docker is slow and pointless
#     since we run `npm ci` inside the container anyway
#   - .next contains previous build output — we rebuild fresh in Docker
#   - .env files contain secrets — they should NEVER be baked into images
#     (secrets are passed at runtime via environment variables)
# ============================================================================

node_modules
.next
.git
.gitignore

# Environment files — secrets must not be baked into images
.env
.env.*

# Dev/test tooling — not needed in production image
playwright-report
test-results
coverage
*.test.ts
*.test.tsx
*.spec.ts

# OS files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Local uploads — production uses MinIO, not local files
public/uploads

# Documentation
README.md
SPEC.md
